    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Crosses used or worn by certain Christians as penance or a symbol of penance having been done. Examples include large crosses carried or dragged by penitents during Holy Week processions, images of crosses emblazoned on the garments of penitents, or cross-shaped objects worn around the neck, sometimes having rough or sharp points intended to injure the skin. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
